<title type="html"><![CDATA[Composing NES music on Mac]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=8405&amp;p=87431#p87431"><![CDATA[
You can convert MIDI to NES music, but you would have to write tools all by yourself (or ask someone), and the result is not going to be top quality. It could provide acceptable quality, though.<br /><br />The easiest way to do it is probably by making a converter that will create data for one of existing music/sfx players for NES, like FamiTone or MUSE. This mean you would only need to make a converter part, and use existing code on NES side, less work.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=4205">Shiru</a> — Tue Dec 13, 2011 1:34 am</p><hr />
